## Summary

| Severity | Count | Key Theme |
|----------|-------|-----------|
| CRITICAL | 4 | MCP tool count mismatch; `model` enum conflict; `08-data-architecture.md` schema contradicts JSONB model; ERD contradicts JSONB model |
| HIGH | 6 | `database-integration-flow.md` entirely pre-pivot; function map references broken anchors; pre-pivot constraint sections; observability phase naming; missing design doc reference; security ADR numbering collision |
| MEDIUM | 8 | Missing DB constraints in migration SQL; `inherit` migration gap; pre-pivot sample responses; no sync protocol architecture doc; flat-vs-JSONB mapping undocumented; stale Redis references |
| LOW | 6 | Broken links; copyright year; path inconsistencies; deprecated references in see-also |

### Recommended Priority

1. **Immediate (blocks implementation):** Fix C-1 through C-4. The `08-data-architecture.md` PostgreSQL schema section and ERD are the most damaging because they present an entirely wrong schema to implementers. The MCP tool count mismatch (C-1) causes confusion about scope.

2. **Before implementation starts:** Resolve C-2 (`inherit` model enum). Either add `inherit` to all API specs or add coercion logic to migration 009. Fix H-1 (`database-integration-flow.md`). Fix M-1 through M-3 (missing constraints in migration SQL).

3. **During implementation:** Address remaining HIGH and MEDIUM items. Fix H-6 (ADR numbering collision) to prevent cross-referencing confusion.
